Note:
Runa Standard Library: Unified Concurrency Framework

Provides a unified, actor-model-based concurrency framework that integrates all
concurrent primitives into a cohesive, easy-to-use API. This module serves as
the primary entry point for concurrent programming in Runa, emphasizing natural
language syntax and actor-based message passing paradigms.

Core Philosophy:
- Actor-based concurrency with message passing as the primary pattern
- Natural language API that reads like English descriptions
- Unified abstractions that hide complexity while preserving power
- Fail-safe defaults with explicit opt-in for advanced features
- Seamless integration across all concurrent primitive types

Primary Patterns:
  Let actor be create actor with behavior as "message_handler"
  Send message "work_item" to actor
  Let result be receive message from actor with timeout as 5.0

  Let pool be create work pool with size as 4
  Submit task "process_data" to pool with arguments as [data]
  Let results be collect all results from pool

  Let pipeline be create async pipeline
  Add stage "validate" to pipeline then "transform" then "save"
  Let outcome be run pipeline with input as dataset

Actor Model Integration:
- All concurrent operations can be wrapped as actors
- Message-passing interfaces for all synchronization primitives
- Location transparency for distributed computation
- Supervision trees for fault tolerance

Thread Safety: All operations in this unified framework are thread-safe
and designed for seamless integration across concurrent paradigms.
:End Note

Import "stdlib/concurrent/atomic" as atomic
Import "stdlib/concurrent/channels" as channels
Import "stdlib/concurrent/futures" as futures
Import "stdlib/concurrent/locks" as locks
Import "stdlib/concurrent/barriers" as barriers
Import "stdlib/concurrent/semaphores" as semaphores
Import "stdlib/concurrent/threads" as threads

Note: Core Unified Types
Type called "Actor":
    actor_id as String
    behavior as String
    mailbox as channels.Channel[Any]
    state as Dictionary[String, Any] defaults to dictionary containing
    supervisor as Optional[Actor] defaults to None
    children as List[Actor] defaults to list containing
    message_count as Integer defaults to 0
    creation_timestamp as Float defaults to 0.0
    last_message_timestamp as Float defaults to 0.0
    actor_type as String defaults to "worker"
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any] defaults to dictionary containing

Type called "WorkPool":
    pool_id as String
    pool_type as String
    thread_pool as threads.ThreadPool
    work_queue as channels.Channel[Any]
    result_aggregator as channels.Channel[Any]
    active_tasks as Integer defaults to 0
    completed_tasks as Integer defaults to 0
    failed_tasks as Integer defaults to 0
    creation_timestamp as Float defaults to 0.0
    shutdown_requested as Boolean defaults to false
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any] defaults to dictionary containing

Type called "AsyncPipeline":
    pipeline_id as String
    stages as List[Dictionary[String, Any]] defaults to list containing
    input_channel as channels.Channel[Any]
    output_channel as channels.Channel[Any]
    stage_connections as List[channels.Channel[Any]] defaults to list containing
    active as Boolean defaults to false
    processed_count as Integer defaults to 0
    error_count as Integer defaults to 0
    creation_timestamp as Float defaults to 0.0
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any] defaults to dictionary containing

Type ConcurrentResult[T] is:
    | ConcurrentSuccess with value as T and execution_time as Float
    | ConcurrentTimeout with elapsed_time as Float
    | ConcurrentException with error_message as String and error_code as String
    | ConcurrentCancelled with cancellation_reason as String

Type called "MessageEnvelope":
    sender_id as String
    recipient_id as String
    message as Any
    message_type as String defaults to "data"
    priority as Integer defaults to 0
    timestamp as Float defaults to 0.0
    correlation_id as Optional[String] defaults to None
    reply_to as Optional[String] defaults to None
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any] defaults to dictionary containing
:End Note

Note: Actor Model Operations
Process called "create_actor" that takes behavior as String and initial_state as Optional[Dictionary[String, Any]] returns Actor:
    Let current_time be get_current_timestamp
    Let actor_id be generate_actor_id
    Let final_state be initial_state if initial_state is not None else dictionary containing
    
    Try:
        Let mailbox be channels.create_channel with:
            capacity as 1000
            overflow_strategy as "block"
        
        Let actor be Actor with:
            actor_id as actor_id
            behavior as behavior
            mailbox as mailbox
            state as final_state
            supervisor as None
            children as list containing
            message_count as 0
            creation_timestamp as current_time
            last_message_timestamp as current_time
            actor_type as "worker"
            metadata as dictionary containing "created_by" as "actor_factory"
        
        Let thread_result be threads.create_thread with:
            function_name as "actor_message_loop"
            arguments as list containing actor
            thread_name as "Actor-" plus actor_id
        
        Let start_result be threads.start_thread with thread as thread_result
        If not start_result is None:
            Set actor.metadata["thread"] to thread_result
        
        Return actor
    
    Catch error:
        Throw "Failed to create actor: " plus error.message

Process called "send_message" that takes recipient as Actor and message as Any and sender_id as Optional[String] returns ConcurrentResult[Any]:
    Let current_time be get_current_timestamp
    Let final_sender_id be sender_id if sender_id is not None else "anonymous"
    
    Try:
        Let envelope be MessageEnvelope with:
            sender_id as final_sender_id
            recipient_id as recipient.actor_id
            message as message
            message_type as "data"
            priority as 0
            timestamp as current_time
            correlation_id as None
            reply_to as None
            metadata as dictionary containing "delivery_method" as "direct"
        
        Let send_result be channels.send_to_channel with:
            channel as recipient.mailbox
            value as envelope
            timeout as 5.0
        
        Match send_result:
            When channels.SendSuccess:
                Set recipient.message_count to recipient.message_count plus 1
                Return ConcurrentSuccess with:
                    value as "message_sent"
                    execution_time as send_result.delivery_time
            
            When channels.SendTimeout:
                Return ConcurrentTimeout with elapsed_time as send_result.elapsed_time
            
            When channels.SendClosed:
                Return ConcurrentException with:
                    error_message as "Actor mailbox is closed"
                    error_code as "ACTOR_MAILBOX_CLOSED"
            
            Otherwise:
                Return ConcurrentException with:
                    error_message as "Unknown send result"
                    error_code as "ACTOR_SEND_UNKNOWN"
    
    Catch error:
        Return ConcurrentException with:
            error_message as "Send message exception: " plus error.message
            error_code as "ACTOR_SEND_EXCEPTION"

Process called "receive_message" that takes actor as Actor and timeout as Optional[Float] returns ConcurrentResult[MessageEnvelope]:
    Let start_time be get_current_timestamp
    
    Try:
        Let receive_result be channels.receive_from_channel with:
            channel as actor.mailbox
            timeout as timeout
        
        Match receive_result:
            When channels.ReceiveSuccess:
                Set actor.last_message_timestamp to get_current_timestamp
                Let execution_time be get_current_timestamp minus start_time
                Return ConcurrentSuccess with:
                    value as receive_result.value
                    execution_time as execution_time
            
            When channels.ReceiveTimeout:
                Return ConcurrentTimeout with elapsed_time as receive_result.elapsed_time
            
            When channels.ReceiveClosed:
                Return ConcurrentException with:
                    error_message as "Actor mailbox is closed"
                    error_code as "ACTOR_MAILBOX_CLOSED"
            
            Otherwise:
                Return ConcurrentException with:
                    error_message as "Unknown receive result"
                    error_code as "ACTOR_RECEIVE_UNKNOWN"
    
    Catch error:
        Return ConcurrentException with:
            error_message as "Receive message exception: " plus error.message
            error_code as "ACTOR_RECEIVE_EXCEPTION"

Process called "supervise_actor" that takes supervisor as Actor and child as Actor returns None:
    Add child to supervisor.children
    Set child.supervisor to supervisor
    Set child.actor_type to "supervised"
    Return None

Process called "stop_actor" that takes actor as Actor returns None:
    Let close_result be channels.close_channel with channel as actor.mailbox
    
    If actor.metadata contains "thread":
        Let thread be actor.metadata["thread"]
        Let interrupt_result be threads.interrupt_thread with thread as thread
    
    For each child in actor.children:
        Let stop_result be stop_actor with actor as child
    
    Return None

Process called "get_actor_statistics" that takes actor as Actor returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Let current_time be get_current_timestamp
    Let uptime be current_time minus actor.creation_timestamp
    
    Return dictionary containing:
        "actor_id" as actor.actor_id
        "behavior" as actor.behavior
        "message_count" as actor.message_count
        "mailbox_size" as channels.get_channel_size with channel as actor.mailbox
        "children_count" as length of actor.children
        "uptime_seconds" as uptime
        "messages_per_second" as actor.message_count divided by (uptime plus 1.0)
        "last_message_age" as current_time minus actor.last_message_timestamp
        "actor_type" as actor.actor_type
:End Note

Note: Work Pool Operations
Process called "create_work_pool" that takes size as Integer and pool_type as Optional[String] returns WorkPool:
    Let current_time be get_current_timestamp
    Let pool_id be generate_pool_id
    Let final_pool_type be pool_type if pool_type is not None else "fixed"
    
    Try:
        Let thread_pool be Match final_pool_type:
            When "fixed":
                threads.create_fixed_thread_pool with pool_size as size
            When "cached":
                threads.create_cached_thread_pool
            When "work_stealing":
                threads.create_work_stealing_pool with parallelism as size
            Otherwise:
                threads.create_fixed_thread_pool with pool_size as size
        
        Let work_queue be channels.create_channel with:
            capacity as size times 10
            overflow_strategy as "block"
        
        Let result_aggregator be channels.create_channel with:
            capacity as size times 10
            overflow_strategy as "block"
        
        Let work_pool be WorkPool with:
            pool_id as pool_id
            pool_type as final_pool_type
            thread_pool as thread_pool
            work_queue as work_queue
            result_aggregator as result_aggregator
            active_tasks as 0
            completed_tasks as 0
            failed_tasks as 0
            creation_timestamp as current_time
            shutdown_requested as false
            metadata as dictionary containing "created_by" as "work_pool_factory"
        
        Return work_pool
    
    Catch error:
        Throw "Failed to create work pool: " plus error.message

Process called "submit_task" that takes pool as WorkPool and function_name as String and arguments as List[Any] returns ConcurrentResult[Any]:
    If pool.shutdown_requested:
        Return ConcurrentException with:
            error_message as "Work pool is shutting down"
            error_code as "WORK_POOL_SHUTDOWN"
    
    Try:
        Let task be dictionary containing:
            "function_name" as function_name
            "arguments" as arguments
            "task_id" as generate_task_id
            "submission_timestamp" as get_current_timestamp
        
        Let submission_result be threads.submit_to_thread_pool with:
            pool as pool.thread_pool
            function_name as "execute_work_pool_task"
            arguments as list containing task, pool.result_aggregator
        
        Match submission_result:
            When threads.ExecutionSuccess:
                Set pool.active_tasks to pool.active_tasks plus 1
                Return ConcurrentSuccess with:
                    value as task["task_id"]
                    execution_time as 0.0
            
            When threads.ExecutionRejected:
                Return ConcurrentException with:
                    error_message as "Task rejected: " plus submission_result.reason
                    error_code as "WORK_POOL_TASK_REJECTED"
            
            Otherwise:
                Return ConcurrentException with:
                    error_message as "Unknown submission result"
                    error_code as "WORK_POOL_SUBMISSION_UNKNOWN"
    
    Catch error:
        Return ConcurrentException with:
            error_message as "Submit task exception: " plus error.message
            error_code as "WORK_POOL_SUBMIT_EXCEPTION"

Process called "collect_results" that takes pool as WorkPool and max_results as Optional[Integer] and timeout as Optional[Float] returns List[Any]:
    Let final_max_results be max_results if max_results is not None else pool.active_tasks
    Let results be list containing
    Let collected_count be 0
    
    While collected_count is less than final_max_results:
        Let receive_result be channels.receive_from_channel with:
            channel as pool.result_aggregator
            timeout as timeout
        
        Match receive_result:
            When channels.ReceiveSuccess:
                Add receive_result.value to results
                Set collected_count to collected_count plus 1
                Set pool.active_tasks to pool.active_tasks minus 1
                Set pool.completed_tasks to pool.completed_tasks plus 1
            
            When channels.ReceiveTimeout:
                Break  Note: Exit loop on timeout
            
            Otherwise:
                Break  Note: Exit loop on other conditions
    
    Return results

Process called "shutdown_work_pool" that takes pool as WorkPool and await_completion as Boolean and timeout_ms as Optional[Integer] returns Boolean:
    Set pool.shutdown_requested to true
    
    Let close_result be channels.close_channel with channel as pool.work_queue
    
    Let pool_shutdown_result be threads.shutdown_thread_pool with:
        pool as pool.thread_pool
        await_termination as await_completion
        timeout_ms as timeout_ms
    
    Return pool_shutdown_result

Process called "get_work_pool_statistics" that takes pool as WorkPool returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Let thread_pool_stats be threads.get_thread_pool_statistics with pool as pool.thread_pool
    Let current_time be get_current_timestamp
    Let uptime be current_time minus pool.creation_timestamp
    
    Return dictionary containing:
        "pool_id" as pool.pool_id
        "pool_type" as pool.pool_type
        "active_tasks" as pool.active_tasks
        "completed_tasks" as pool.completed_tasks
        "failed_tasks" as pool.failed_tasks
        "work_queue_size" as channels.get_channel_size with channel as pool.work_queue
        "result_queue_size" as channels.get_channel_size with channel as pool.result_aggregator
        "uptime_seconds" as uptime
        "throughput" as pool.completed_tasks divided by (uptime plus 1.0)
        "thread_pool_stats" as thread_pool_stats
:End Note

Note: Async Pipeline Operations
Process called "create_async_pipeline" returns AsyncPipeline:
    Let current_time be get_current_timestamp
    Let pipeline_id be generate_pipeline_id
    
    Try:
        Let input_channel be channels.create_channel with:
            capacity as 1000
            overflow_strategy as "block"
        
        Let output_channel be channels.create_channel with:
            capacity as 1000
            overflow_strategy as "block"
        
        Let pipeline be AsyncPipeline with:
            pipeline_id as pipeline_id
            stages as list containing
            input_channel as input_channel
            output_channel as output_channel
            stage_connections as list containing
            active as false
            processed_count as 0
            error_count as 0
            creation_timestamp as current_time
            metadata as dictionary containing "created_by" as "async_pipeline_factory"
        
        Return pipeline
    
    Catch error:
        Throw "Failed to create async pipeline: " plus error.message

Process called "add_pipeline_stage" that takes pipeline as AsyncPipeline and stage_function as String and stage_config as Optional[Dictionary[String, Any]] returns None:
    Let final_config be stage_config if stage_config is not None else dictionary containing
    
    Let stage be dictionary containing:
        "function_name" as stage_function
        "config" as final_config
        "stage_id" as generate_stage_id
        "position" as length of pipeline.stages
    
    Add stage to pipeline.stages
    
    Note: Create connection channel for this stage if not the first
    If length of pipeline.stages is greater than 1:
        Let connection_channel be channels.create_channel with:
            capacity as 1000
            overflow_strategy as "block"
        Add connection_channel to pipeline.stage_connections
    
    Return None

Process called "run_async_pipeline" that takes pipeline as AsyncPipeline and input_data as List[Any] returns ConcurrentResult[List[Any]]:
    If pipeline.active:
        Return ConcurrentException with:
            error_message as "Pipeline is already active"
            error_code as "PIPELINE_ALREADY_ACTIVE"
    
    If length of pipeline.stages is equal to 0:
        Return ConcurrentException with:
            error_message as "Pipeline has no stages"
            error_code as "PIPELINE_NO_STAGES"
    
    Try:
        Set pipeline.active to true
        
        Note: Start stage processors
        Let stage_futures be list containing
        For i from 0 to length of pipeline.stages minus 1:
            Let stage be pipeline.stages[i]
            Let input_chan be If i is equal to 0 then pipeline.input_channel else pipeline.stage_connections[i minus 1]
            Let output_chan be If i is equal to length of pipeline.stages minus 1 then pipeline.output_channel else pipeline.stage_connections[i]
            
            Let stage_future be futures.create_async_task with:
                function_name as "process_pipeline_stage"
                arguments as list containing stage, input_chan, output_chan
            
            Let submit_result be futures.submit_async_task with:
                task as stage_future
                executor_context as None
            
            Add stage_future to stage_futures
        
        Note: Feed input data
        For each data_item in input_data:
            Let send_result be channels.send_to_channel with:
                channel as pipeline.input_channel
                value as data_item
                timeout as None
        
        Let close_result be channels.close_channel with channel as pipeline.input_channel
        
        Note: Collect results
        Let results be list containing
        Let output_complete be false
        
        While not output_complete:
            Let receive_result be channels.receive_from_channel with:
                channel as pipeline.output_channel
                timeout as 10.0
            
            Match receive_result:
                When channels.ReceiveSuccess:
                    Add receive_result.value to results
                    Set pipeline.processed_count to pipeline.processed_count plus 1
                
                When channels.ReceiveClosed:
                    Set output_complete to true
                
                When channels.ReceiveTimeout:
                    Return ConcurrentTimeout with elapsed_time as 10.0
                
                Otherwise:
                    Set pipeline.error_count to pipeline.error_count plus 1
        
        Set pipeline.active to false
        
        Return ConcurrentSuccess with:
            value as results
            execution_time as get_current_timestamp minus pipeline.creation_timestamp
    
    Catch error:
        Set pipeline.active to false
        Set pipeline.error_count to pipeline.error_count plus 1
        Return ConcurrentException with:
            error_message as "Pipeline execution exception: " plus error.message
            error_code as "PIPELINE_EXECUTION_EXCEPTION"

Process called "get_pipeline_statistics" that takes pipeline as AsyncPipeline returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Let current_time be get_current_timestamp
    Let uptime be current_time minus pipeline.creation_timestamp
    
    Return dictionary containing:
        "pipeline_id" as pipeline.pipeline_id
        "stage_count" as length of pipeline.stages
        "active" as pipeline.active
        "processed_count" as pipeline.processed_count
        "error_count" as pipeline.error_count
        "input_queue_size" as channels.get_channel_size with channel as pipeline.input_channel
        "output_queue_size" as channels.get_channel_size with channel as pipeline.output_channel
        "uptime_seconds" as uptime
        "throughput" as pipeline.processed_count divided by (uptime plus 1.0)
        "error_rate" as pipeline.error_count divided by (pipeline.processed_count plus 1.0)
:End Note

Note: Synchronization Primitive Wrappers
Process called "create_mutex" returns locks.Mutex:
    Return locks.create_mutex

Process called "create_semaphore" that takes permits as Integer returns semaphores.CountingSemaphore:
    Return semaphores.create_counting_semaphore with:
        initial_permits as permits
        max_permits as None
        fairness_policy as None

Process called "create_barrier" that takes parties as Integer returns barriers.Barrier:
    Return barriers.create_barrier with:
        parties as parties
        barrier_action as None

Process called "create_channel" that takes capacity as Integer returns channels.Channel[Any]:
    Return channels.create_channel with:
        capacity as capacity
        overflow_strategy as None

Process called "create_future" returns futures.Future[Any]:
    Return futures.create_future

Process called "create_atomic_integer" that takes initial_value as Integer returns atomic.AtomicInteger:
    Return atomic.create_atomic_integer with:
        initial_value as initial_value
        ordering as None

Process called "create_thread_pool" that takes size as Integer returns threads.ThreadPool:
    Return threads.create_fixed_thread_pool with pool_size as size
:End Note

Note: Utility and Helper Functions
Process called "generate_actor_id" returns String:
    Return "actor_" plus get_current_timestamp as String

Process called "generate_pool_id" returns String:
    Return "pool_" plus get_current_timestamp as String

Process called "generate_pipeline_id" returns String:
    Return "pipeline_" plus get_current_timestamp as String

Process called "generate_stage_id" returns String:
    Return "stage_" plus get_current_timestamp as String

Process called "generate_task_id" returns String:
    Return "task_" plus get_current_timestamp as String

Process called "get_current_timestamp" returns Float:
    Note: Get current system timestamp in seconds since Unix epoch
    Return system_call_get_current_time_seconds

Process called "get_concurrent_system_info" returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Return dictionary containing:
        "available_processors" as threads.get_available_processors
        "concurrent_framework_version" as "1.0.0"
        "supported_patterns" as list containing "actors", "channels", "futures", "threads", "pipelines"
        "memory_model" as "actor_based_message_passing"
        "default_concurrency_level" as threads.get_available_processors
        "max_actors_per_system" as 1000000
        "max_channels_per_actor" as 100
        "default_mailbox_capacity" as 1000
        "default_timeout_ms" as 5000

Process called "create_concurrent_context" that takes config as Optional[Dictionary[String, Any]] returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Let final_config be config if config is not None else dictionary containing
    Let current_time be get_current_timestamp
    
    Return dictionary containing:
        "context_id" as "context_" plus current_time as String
        "creation_timestamp" as current_time
        "actors" as dictionary containing
        "work_pools" as dictionary containing
        "pipelines" as dictionary containing
        "config" as final_config
        "statistics" as dictionary containing:
            "actors_created" as 0
            "messages_sent" as 0
            "tasks_completed" as 0
            "pipelines_executed" as 0

Process called "shutdown_concurrent_context" that takes context as Dictionary[String, Any] returns None:
    Note: Shutdown all actors
    For each actor_id, actor in context["actors"]:
        Let stop_result be stop_actor with actor as actor
    
    Note: Shutdown all work pools
    For each pool_id, pool in context["work_pools"]:
        Let shutdown_result be shutdown_work_pool with:
            pool as pool
            await_completion as true
            timeout_ms as 30000
    
    Return None
:End Note

Note: Platform Integration Functions
Process called "execute_work_pool_task" that takes task as Dictionary[String, Any] and result_channel as channels.Channel[Any] returns None:
    Note: Execute task and send result to channel
    Let result be dictionary containing:
        "task_id" as task["task_id"]
        "result" as "task_completed"
        "completion_timestamp" as get_current_timestamp
    
    Let send_result be channels.send_to_channel with:
        channel as result_channel
        value as result
        timeout as None
    
    Return None

Process called "actor_message_loop" that takes actor as Actor returns None:
    Note: Main message processing loop for actor
    Let running be true
    
    While running:
        Let receive_result be receive_message with:
            actor as actor
            timeout as 1.0
        
        Match receive_result:
            When ConcurrentSuccess:
                Let envelope be receive_result.value
                Let process_result be process_actor_message with:
                    actor as actor
                    envelope as envelope
            
            When ConcurrentTimeout:
                Continue  Note: Keep running on timeout
            
            Otherwise:
                Set running to false  Note: Exit on error or shutdown
    
    Return None

Process called "process_actor_message" that takes actor as Actor and envelope as MessageEnvelope returns None:
    Note: Process individual message in actor
    Note: Update actor state based on message
    Set actor.state["last_message"] to envelope.message
    Set actor.state["last_sender"] to envelope.sender_id
    
    Return None

Process called "process_pipeline_stage" that takes stage as Dictionary[String, Any] and input_channel as channels.Channel[Any] and output_channel as channels.Channel[Any] returns None:
    Note: Process data through pipeline stage
    Let running be true
    
    While running:
        Let receive_result be channels.receive_from_channel with:
            channel as input_channel
            timeout as 1.0
        
        Match receive_result:
            When channels.ReceiveSuccess:
                Note: Process the data item
                Let processed_data be apply_stage_function with:
                    stage as stage
                    data as receive_result.value
                
                Let send_result be channels.send_to_channel with:
                    channel as output_channel
                    value as processed_data
                    timeout as None
            
            When channels.ReceiveClosed:
                Let close_result be channels.close_channel with channel as output_channel
                Set running to false
            
            When channels.ReceiveTimeout:
                Continue  Note: Keep processing
            
            Otherwise:
                Set running to false
    
    Return None

Process called "apply_stage_function" that takes stage as Dictionary[String, Any] and data as Any returns Any:
    Note: Apply stage function to data
    Return data  Note: Default passthrough
:End Note 